{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1000,"text":"I want you to take a trip with me."},{"time":3000,"text":"Picture yourself driving"},{"time":5000,"text":"down a small road in Africa,"},{"time":7000,"text":"and as you drive along, you look off to the side,"},{"time":10000,"text":"and this is what you see:"},{"time":12000,"text":"you see a field of graves."},{"time":14000,"text":"And you stop, and you get out of your car and you take a picture."},{"time":16000,"text":"And you go into the town,"},{"time":18000,"text":"and you inquire, \"What's going on here?\""},{"time":20000,"text":"and people are initially reluctant to tell you."},{"time":22000,"text":"And then someone says,"},{"time":24000,"text":"\"These are the recent AIDS deaths in our community.\""},{"time":28000,"text":"HIV isn't like other medical conditions;"},{"time":30000,"text":"it's stigmatizing."},{"time":32000,"text":"People are reluctant to talk about it --"},{"time":35000,"text":"there's a fear associated with it."},{"time":37000,"text":"And I'm going to talk about HIV today,"},{"time":39000,"text":"about the deaths,"},{"time":41000,"text":"about the stigma."},{"time":43000,"text":"It's a medical story, but more than that, it's a social story."}]},{"cues":[{"time":48000,"text":"This map depicts the global distribution of HIV."},{"time":51000,"text":"And as you can see,"},{"time":53000,"text":"Africa has a disproportionate share of the infection."},{"time":55000,"text":"There are 33 million people"},{"time":57000,"text":"living with HIV in the world today."},{"time":59000,"text":"Of these, two-thirds, 22 million"},{"time":62000,"text":"are living in sub-Saharan Africa."},{"time":65000,"text":"There are 1.4 million pregnant women"},{"time":68000,"text":"in low- and middle-income countries living with HIV"},{"time":71000,"text":"and of these, 90 percent"},{"time":73000,"text":"are in sub-Saharan Africa."},{"time":77000,"text":"We talk about things in relative terms."},{"time":79000,"text":"And I'm going to talk about annual pregnancies"},{"time":81000,"text":"and HIV-positive mothers."},{"time":83000,"text":"The United States -- a large country --"},{"time":85000,"text":"each year, 7,000 mothers with HIV"},{"time":88000,"text":"who give birth to a child."},{"time":91000,"text":"But you go to Rwanda -- a very small country --"},{"time":94000,"text":"8,000 mothers with HIV who are pregnant."},{"time":98000,"text":"And then you go to Baragwanath Hospital,"},{"time":101000,"text":"outside of Johannesburg in South Africa,"},{"time":104000,"text":"and 8,000 HIV-positive pregnant women"},{"time":106000,"text":"giving birth --"},{"time":108000,"text":"a hospital the same as a country."},{"time":111000,"text":"And to realize that this is just the tip of an iceberg"},{"time":114000,"text":"that when you compare"},{"time":116000,"text":"everything here to South Africa, it just pales,"},{"time":118000,"text":"because in South Africa,"},{"time":121000,"text":"each year 300,000 mothers with HIV"},{"time":124000,"text":"give birth to children."}]},{"cues":[{"time":128000,"text":"So we talk about PMTCT,"},{"time":130000,"text":"and we refer to PMTCT, prevention of mother to child transmission."},{"time":133000,"text":"I think there's an assumption amongst most people in the public"},{"time":136000,"text":"that if a mother is HIV-positive,"},{"time":138000,"text":"she's going to infect her child."},{"time":140000,"text":"The reality is really, very different."},{"time":143000,"text":"In resource-rich countries,"},{"time":145000,"text":"with all the tests and treatment we currently have,"},{"time":147000,"text":"less than two percent of babies are born HIV-positive --"},{"time":150000,"text":"98 percent of babies are born HIV-negative."},{"time":154000,"text":"And yet, the reality in resource-poor countries,"},{"time":156000,"text":"in the absence of tests and treatment,"},{"time":158000,"text":"40 percent -- 40 percent of children are infected --"},{"time":161000,"text":"40 percent versus two percent --"},{"time":163000,"text":"an enormous difference."},{"time":165000,"text":"So these programs --"},{"time":167000,"text":"and I'm going to refer to PMTCT though my talk --"},{"time":169000,"text":"these prevention programs,"},{"time":171000,"text":"simply, they're the tests and the drugs that we give to mothers"},{"time":174000,"text":"to prevent them from infecting their babies,"},{"time":177000,"text":"and also the medicines we give to mothers"},{"time":179000,"text":"to keep them healthy and alive to raise their children."},{"time":181000,"text":"So it's the test a mother gets when she comes in."},{"time":183000,"text":"It's the drugs she receives"},{"time":185000,"text":"to protect the baby that's inside the uterus and during delivery."},{"time":188000,"text":"It's the guidance she gets around infant feeding"},{"time":190000,"text":"and safer sex."},{"time":192000,"text":"It's an entire package of services,"},{"time":195000,"text":"and it works."}]},{"cues":[{"time":197000,"text":"So in the United States,"},{"time":199000,"text":"since the advent of treatment in the middle of the 1990s,"},{"time":202000,"text":"there's been an 80-percent decline"},{"time":204000,"text":"in the number of HIV-infected children."},{"time":206000,"text":"Less than 100 babies are born with HIV"},{"time":208000,"text":"each year in the United States"},{"time":210000,"text":"and yet, still,"},{"time":212000,"text":"over 400,000 children"},{"time":215000,"text":"are born every year in the world today with HIV."},{"time":219000,"text":"What does that mean?"},{"time":221000,"text":"It means 1,100 children infected each day --"},{"time":224000,"text":"1,100 children each day, infected with HIV."},{"time":227000,"text":"And where do they come from?"},{"time":229000,"text":"Well, less than one comes from the United States."},{"time":233000,"text":"One, on average, comes from Europe."},{"time":237000,"text":"100 come from Asia and the Pacific."},{"time":241000,"text":"And each day,"},{"time":243000,"text":"a thousand babies -- a thousand babies"},{"time":246000,"text":"are born each day with HIV in Africa."}]},{"cues":[{"time":251000,"text":"So again, I look at the globe here"},{"time":253000,"text":"and the disproportionate share of HIV in Africa."},{"time":256000,"text":"And let's look at another map."},{"time":258000,"text":"And here, again, we see"},{"time":260000,"text":"Africa has a disproportionate share of the numbers of doctors."},{"time":263000,"text":"That thin sliver you see here, that's Africa."},{"time":266000,"text":"And it's the same with nurses."},{"time":269000,"text":"The truth is sub-Saharan Africa"},{"time":271000,"text":"has 24 percent"},{"time":273000,"text":"of the global disease burden"},{"time":275000,"text":"and yet only three percent of the world's health care workers."},{"time":278000,"text":"That means doctors and nurses"},{"time":280000,"text":"simply don't have the time to take care of patients."},{"time":283000,"text":"A nurse in a busy clinic"},{"time":285000,"text":"will see 50 to 100 patients in a day,"},{"time":287000,"text":"which leaves her just minutes per patient --"},{"time":289000,"text":"minutes per patient."},{"time":291000,"text":"And so when we look at these PMTCT programs, what does it mean?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":294000,"text":"Well, back in 2001,"},{"time":296000,"text":"when there was just a simple test"},{"time":298000,"text":"and a single dose of a drug,"},{"time":300000,"text":"a nurse, in the course of her few minutes with a patient,"},{"time":303000,"text":"would have to counsel for the HIV test, perform the HIV test,"},{"time":306000,"text":"explain the results, dispense a single dose of the drug, Nevirapine,"},{"time":309000,"text":"explain how to take it, discuss infant feeding options, reinforce infant feeding,"},{"time":312000,"text":"and test the baby -- in minutes."},{"time":315000,"text":"Well, fortunately since 2001,"},{"time":317000,"text":"we've got new treatments, new tests,"},{"time":319000,"text":"and we're far more successful,"},{"time":321000,"text":"but we don't have any more nurses."},{"time":323000,"text":"And so these are the tests"},{"time":326000,"text":"a nurse now has to do"},{"time":328000,"text":"in those same few minutes."},{"time":330000,"text":"It's not possible --"},{"time":332000,"text":"it doesn't work."},{"time":334000,"text":"And so we need to find"},{"time":336000,"text":"better ways of providing care."}]},{"cues":[{"time":341000,"text":"This is a picture of a maternal health clinic in Africa --"},{"time":344000,"text":"mothers coming, pregnant and with their babies."},{"time":347000,"text":"These women are here for care,"},{"time":349000,"text":"but we know that just doing a test,"},{"time":351000,"text":"just giving someone a drug,"},{"time":353000,"text":"it's not enough."},{"time":356000,"text":"Meds don't equal medical care."},{"time":359000,"text":"Doctors and nurses, frankly,"},{"time":361000,"text":"don't have the time or skills"},{"time":363000,"text":"to tell people what to do in ways they understand."},{"time":365000,"text":"I'm a doctor -- I tell people things to do,"},{"time":368000,"text":"and I expect them to follow my guidance --"},{"time":370000,"text":"because I'm a doctor; I went to Harvard --"},{"time":372000,"text":"but the reality is,"},{"time":374000,"text":"if I tell a patient, \"You should have safer sex."},{"time":376000,"text":"You should always use a condom,\""},{"time":378000,"text":"and yet, in her relationship, she's not empowered --"},{"time":381000,"text":"what's going to happen?"},{"time":383000,"text":"If I tell her to take her medicines every day"},{"time":386000,"text":"and yet, no one in the household knows about her illness, so"},{"time":389000,"text":"it's just not going to work."},{"time":392000,"text":"And so we need to do more,"},{"time":394000,"text":"we need to do it differently,"},{"time":396000,"text":"we need to do it in ways that are affordable"},{"time":399000,"text":"and accessible and can be taken to scale,"},{"time":401000,"text":"which means it can be done everywhere."}]},{"cues":[{"time":404000,"text":"So, I want to tell you a story --"},{"time":407000,"text":"I want to take you on a little trip."},{"time":409000,"text":"Imagine yourself, if you can,"},{"time":411000,"text":"you're a young woman in Africa, you're going to the hospital or clinic."},{"time":414000,"text":"You go in for a test"},{"time":416000,"text":"and you find out that you're pregnant, and you're delighted."},{"time":418000,"text":"And then they give you another test"},{"time":420000,"text":"and they tell you you're HIV-positive, and you're devastated."},{"time":423000,"text":"And the nurse takes you into a room,"},{"time":425000,"text":"and she tells you about the tests"},{"time":427000,"text":"and HIV and the medicines you can take"},{"time":429000,"text":"and how to take care of yourself and your baby,"},{"time":431000,"text":"and you hear none of it."},{"time":433000,"text":"All you're hearing is, \"I'm going to die,"},{"time":435000,"text":"and my baby is going to die.\""},{"time":437000,"text":"And then you're out on the street, and you don't know where to go."},{"time":439000,"text":"And you don't know who you can talk to,"},{"time":441000,"text":"because the truth is, HIV is so stigmatizing"},{"time":444000,"text":"that if you partner, your family, anyone in your home,"},{"time":447000,"text":"you're likely to be thrown out"},{"time":449000,"text":"without any means of support."},{"time":451000,"text":"And this -- this is the face and story"},{"time":453000,"text":"of HIV in Africa today."}]},{"cues":[{"time":456000,"text":"But we're here to talk about possible solutions"},{"time":459000,"text":"and some good news."},{"time":461000,"text":"And I want to change the story a little bit."},{"time":464000,"text":"Take the same mother, and the nurse, after she gives her her test,"},{"time":467000,"text":"takes her to a room."},{"time":469000,"text":"The door opens and there's a room full of mothers, mothers with babies,"},{"time":472000,"text":"and they're sitting, and they're talking, they're listening."},{"time":474000,"text":"They're drinking tea, they're having sandwiches."},{"time":477000,"text":"And she goes inside, and woman comes up to her and says,"},{"time":479000,"text":"\"Welcome to mothers2mothers."},{"time":481000,"text":"Have a seat. You're safe here."},{"time":484000,"text":"We're all HIV-positive."},{"time":486000,"text":"You're going to be okay. You're going to live."},{"time":489000,"text":"Your baby is going to be HIV-negative.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":494000,"text":"We view mothers"},{"time":496000,"text":"as a community's single greatest resource."},{"time":498000,"text":"Mothers take care of the children, take care of the home."},{"time":501000,"text":"So often the men are gone."},{"time":503000,"text":"They're working, or they're not part of the household."},{"time":506000,"text":"Our organization, mothers2mothers,"},{"time":508000,"text":"enlists women with HIV"},{"time":510000,"text":"as care providers."},{"time":512000,"text":"We bring mothers who have HIV,"},{"time":514000,"text":"who've been through these PMTCT programs"},{"time":516000,"text":"in the very facilities,"},{"time":518000,"text":"to come back and work side by side with doctors and nurses"},{"time":521000,"text":"as part of the health care team."},{"time":523000,"text":"These mothers, we call them mentor mothers,"},{"time":526000,"text":"are able to engage women"},{"time":528000,"text":"who, just like themselves, pregnant with babies,"},{"time":530000,"text":"have found out about being HIV-positive,"},{"time":532000,"text":"who need support and education."},{"time":535000,"text":"And they support them around the diagnosis"},{"time":537000,"text":"and educate them about how to take their medicines,"},{"time":539000,"text":"how to take care of themselves,"},{"time":541000,"text":"how to take care of their babies."},{"time":544000,"text":"Consider: if you needed surgery,"},{"time":547000,"text":"you would want the best possible technical surgeon, right?"},{"time":551000,"text":"But if you wanted to understand"},{"time":553000,"text":"what that surgery would do to your life,"},{"time":555000,"text":"you'd like to engage someone,"},{"time":557000,"text":"someone who's had the procedure."},{"time":559000,"text":"Patients are experts on their own experience,"},{"time":562000,"text":"and they can share that experience with others."},{"time":566000,"text":"This is the medical care that goes beyond just medicines."}]},{"cues":[{"time":570000,"text":"So the mothers who work for us,"},{"time":572000,"text":"they come from the communities in which they work."},{"time":574000,"text":"They're hired -- they're paid as professional members of the health care teams,"},{"time":577000,"text":"just like doctors and nurses."},{"time":579000,"text":"And we open bank accounts for them"},{"time":581000,"text":"and they're paid directly into the accounts,"},{"time":583000,"text":"because their money's protected;"},{"time":585000,"text":"the men can't take it away from them."},{"time":588000,"text":"They go through two to three weeks"},{"time":590000,"text":"of rigorous curriculum-based education, training."},{"time":593000,"text":"Now, doctors and nurses -- they too get trained."},{"time":596000,"text":"But so often, they only get trained once,"},{"time":598000,"text":"so they're not aware of new medicines,"},{"time":600000,"text":"new guidelines as they come out."},{"time":602000,"text":"Our mentor mothers get trained every single year"},{"time":604000,"text":"and retrained."},{"time":606000,"text":"And so doctors and nurses --"},{"time":608000,"text":"they look up to them as experts."},{"time":611000,"text":"Imagine that: a woman, a former patient,"},{"time":614000,"text":"being able to educate her doctor for the first time"},{"time":616000,"text":"and educate the other patients"},{"time":618000,"text":"that she's taking care of."}]},{"cues":[{"time":621000,"text":"Our organization has three goals."},{"time":623000,"text":"The first, to prevent mother-to-child transmission."},{"time":627000,"text":"The second: keep mothers healthy, keep mothers alive,"},{"time":630000,"text":"keep the children alive --"},{"time":632000,"text":"no more orphans."},{"time":634000,"text":"And the third, and maybe the most grand,"},{"time":637000,"text":"is to find ways to empower women,"},{"time":641000,"text":"enable them to fight the stigma"},{"time":643000,"text":"and to live positive and productive lives with HIV."},{"time":647000,"text":"So how do we do it?"},{"time":649000,"text":"Well, maybe the most important engagement"},{"time":651000,"text":"is the one-to-one,"},{"time":653000,"text":"seeing patients one-to-one, educating them, supporting them,"},{"time":656000,"text":"explaining how they can take care of themselves."},{"time":659000,"text":"We go beyond that;"},{"time":661000,"text":"we try to bring in the husbands, the partners."},{"time":664000,"text":"In Africa, it's very, very hard to engage men."},{"time":667000,"text":"Men are not frequently part of pregnancy care."},{"time":671000,"text":"But in Rwanda, in one country,"},{"time":673000,"text":"they've got a policy"},{"time":675000,"text":"that a woman can't come for care"},{"time":677000,"text":"unless she brings the father of the baby with her --"},{"time":679000,"text":"that's the rule."},{"time":681000,"text":"And so the father and the mother, together,"},{"time":683000,"text":"go through the counseling and the testing."},{"time":686000,"text":"The father and the mother, together, they get the results."},{"time":688000,"text":"And this is so important in breaking through the stigma."}]},{"cues":[{"time":692000,"text":"Disclosure is so central to prevention."},{"time":695000,"text":"How do you have safer sex, how do you use a condom regularly"},{"time":698000,"text":"if there hasn't been disclosure?"},{"time":700000,"text":"Disclosure is so important to treatment,"},{"time":703000,"text":"because again, people need the support of family members and friends"},{"time":706000,"text":"to take their medicines regularly."},{"time":709000,"text":"We also work in groups."},{"time":711000,"text":"Now the groups, it's not like me lecturing,"},{"time":713000,"text":"but what happens is women, they come together --"},{"time":716000,"text":"under the support and guidance of our mentor mothers --"},{"time":718000,"text":"they come together, and they share their personal experiences."},{"time":721000,"text":"And it's through the sharing"},{"time":723000,"text":"that people get tactics of how to take care of themselves,"},{"time":725000,"text":"how to disclose how to take medicines."},{"time":729000,"text":"And then there's the community outreach,"},{"time":731000,"text":"engaging women in their communities."},{"time":734000,"text":"If we can change the way"},{"time":736000,"text":"households believe and think,"},{"time":738000,"text":"we can change the way communities believe and think."},{"time":741000,"text":"And if we can change enough communities,"},{"time":743000,"text":"we can change national attitudes."},{"time":745000,"text":"We can change national attitudes to women"},{"time":747000,"text":"and national attitudes to HIV."},{"time":750000,"text":"The hardest barrier really is around stigma reduction."},{"time":752000,"text":"We have the medicines, we have the tests,"},{"time":754000,"text":"but how do you reduce the stigma?"},{"time":757000,"text":"And it's important about disclosure."}]},{"cues":[{"time":759000,"text":"So, a couple years ago, one of the mentor mothers came back,"},{"time":761000,"text":"and she told me a story."},{"time":763000,"text":"She had been asked by one of the clients"},{"time":765000,"text":"to go to the home of the client,"},{"time":767000,"text":"because the client wanted to tell the mother and her brothers and sisters"},{"time":770000,"text":"about her HIV status,"},{"time":772000,"text":"and she was afraid to go by herself."},{"time":774000,"text":"And so the mentor mother went along with."},{"time":776000,"text":"And the patient walked into the house"},{"time":778000,"text":"and said to her mother and siblings,"},{"time":781000,"text":"\"I have something to tell you. I'm HIV-positive.\""},{"time":784000,"text":"And everybody was quiet."},{"time":786000,"text":"And then her oldest brother stood up and said,"},{"time":788000,"text":"\"I too have something to tell you."},{"time":790000,"text":"I'm HIV-positive."},{"time":792000,"text":"I've been afraid to tell everybody.\""},{"time":795000,"text":"And then this older sister stood up and said,"},{"time":797000,"text":"\"I too am living with the virus,"},{"time":800000,"text":"and I've been ashamed.\""},{"time":802000,"text":"And then her younger brother stood up and said,"},{"time":805000,"text":"\"I'm also positive."},{"time":807000,"text":"I thought you were going to throw me out of the family.\""},{"time":809000,"text":"And you see where this is going."},{"time":811000,"text":"The last sister stood up and said, \"I'm also positive."},{"time":813000,"text":"I thought you were going to hate me.\""},{"time":815000,"text":"And there they were, all of them together for the first time"},{"time":817000,"text":"being able to share this experience for the first time"},{"time":820000,"text":"and to support each other for the first time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":823000,"text":"(Video) Female Narrator: Women come to us,"},{"time":825000,"text":"and they are crying and scared."},{"time":828000,"text":"I tell them my story,"},{"time":830000,"text":"that I am HIV-positive,"},{"time":833000,"text":"but my child is HIV-negative."},{"time":836000,"text":"I tell them, \"You are going to make it,"},{"time":839000,"text":"and you will raise a healthy baby.\""},{"time":843000,"text":"I am proof that there is hope."}]},{"cues":[{"time":849000,"text":"Mitchell Besser: Remember the images I showed you"},{"time":851000,"text":"of how few doctors and nurses there are in Africa."},{"time":853000,"text":"And it is a crisis in health care systems."},{"time":856000,"text":"Even as we have more tests and more drugs,"},{"time":858000,"text":"we can't reach people; we don't have enough providers."},{"time":860000,"text":"So we talk in terms of what we call task-shifting."},{"time":862000,"text":"Task-shifting is traditionally"},{"time":864000,"text":"when you take health care services from one provider"},{"time":866000,"text":"and have another provider do it."},{"time":868000,"text":"Typically, it's a doctor giving a job to a nurse."},{"time":870000,"text":"And the issue in Africa"},{"time":872000,"text":"is that there are fewer nurses, really than doctors,"},{"time":874000,"text":"and so we need to find new paradigm for health care."},{"time":877000,"text":"How do you build a better health care system?"},{"time":880000,"text":"We've chosen to redefine the health care system"},{"time":882000,"text":"as a doctor, a nurse and a mentor mother."},{"time":884000,"text":"And so what nurses do"},{"time":886000,"text":"is that they ask the mentor mothers to explain"},{"time":888000,"text":"how to take the drugs, the side effects."},{"time":890000,"text":"They delegate education about infant feeding,"},{"time":893000,"text":"family planning, safer sex,"},{"time":895000,"text":"actions that nurses simple just don't have time for."}]},{"cues":[{"time":900000,"text":"So we go back to the prevention of mother to child transmission."},{"time":903000,"text":"The world is increasingly seeing these programs"},{"time":905000,"text":"as the bridge to comprehensive maternal and child health."},{"time":908000,"text":"And our organization"},{"time":910000,"text":"helps women across that bridge."},{"time":912000,"text":"The care doesn't stop when the baby's born --"},{"time":914000,"text":"we deal with the ongoing health of the mother and baby,"},{"time":917000,"text":"ensuring that they live healthy,"},{"time":920000,"text":"successful lives."}]},{"cues":[{"time":922000,"text":"Our organization works on three levels."},{"time":925000,"text":"The first, at the patient level --"},{"time":927000,"text":"mothers and babies keeping babies from getting HIV,"},{"time":929000,"text":"keeping mothers healthy to raise them."},{"time":932000,"text":"The second, communities --"},{"time":934000,"text":"empowering women."},{"time":936000,"text":"They become leaders within their communities."},{"time":939000,"text":"They change the way communities think --"},{"time":941000,"text":"we need to change attitudes to HIV."},{"time":944000,"text":"We need to change attitudes to women in Africa."},{"time":946000,"text":"We have to do that."},{"time":948000,"text":"And then rework the level of the health care systems,"},{"time":951000,"text":"building stronger health care systems."},{"time":953000,"text":"Our health care systems are broken."},{"time":955000,"text":"They're not going to work the way they're currently designed."},{"time":958000,"text":"And so doctors and nurses"},{"time":960000,"text":"who need to try to change people's behaviors"},{"time":962000,"text":"don't have the skills, don't have the time --"},{"time":964000,"text":"our mentor mothers do."},{"time":966000,"text":"And so in redefining the health care teams by bringing the mentor mothers in,"},{"time":969000,"text":"we can do that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":972000,"text":"I started the program in Capetown, South Africa"},{"time":975000,"text":"back in 2001."},{"time":977000,"text":"It was at that point, just the spark of an idea."},{"time":980000,"text":"Referencing Steven Johnson's very lovely speech yesterday"},{"time":983000,"text":"on where ideas come from,"},{"time":986000,"text":"I was in the shower at the time --"},{"time":989000,"text":"I was alone."},{"time":991000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":995000,"text":"The program is now working in nine countries,"},{"time":998000,"text":"we have 670 program sites,"},{"time":1001000,"text":"we're seeing about 230,000"},{"time":1004000,"text":"women every month,"},{"time":1006000,"text":"we're employing 1,600 mentor mothers,"},{"time":1009000,"text":"and last year, they enrolled"},{"time":1011000,"text":"300,000 HIV-positive pregnant women and mothers."},{"time":1014000,"text":"That is 20 percent"},{"time":1017000,"text":"of the global HIV-positive pregnant women --"},{"time":1020000,"text":"20 percent of the world."},{"time":1022000,"text":"What's extraordinary is how simple the premise is."},{"time":1024000,"text":"Mothers with HIV caring for mothers with HIV."},{"time":1027000,"text":"Past patients taking care of present patients."},{"time":1029000,"text":"And empowerment through employment --"},{"time":1031000,"text":"reducing stigma."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1033000,"text":"(Video) Female Narrator: There is hope,"},{"time":1035000,"text":"hope that one day"},{"time":1037000,"text":"we shall win this fight"},{"time":1039000,"text":"against HIV and AIDS."},{"time":1042000,"text":"Each person must know"},{"time":1044000,"text":"their HIV status."},{"time":1047000,"text":"Those who are HIV-negative"},{"time":1049000,"text":"must know how to stay negative."},{"time":1053000,"text":"Those who are HIV-infected"},{"time":1056000,"text":"must know how"},{"time":1058000,"text":"to take care of themselves."},{"time":1061000,"text":"HIV-positive pregnant women"},{"time":1063000,"text":"must get PMTCT services"},{"time":1066000,"text":"in order to have"},{"time":1068000,"text":"HIV-negative babies."},{"time":1070000,"text":"All of this is possible,"},{"time":1073000,"text":"if we each contribute to this fight."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1078000,"text":"MB: Simple solutions to complex problems."},{"time":1081000,"text":"Mothers caring for mothers."},{"time":1083000,"text":"It's transformational."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1085000,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1087000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}